 potential in key areas of astronomy astrophysics and fundamental physics research these include the study of the origin of cosmic rays and their impact on the constituents of the universe the investigation of the nature and variety of black hole particle accelerators and the inquiry into the ultimate nature of matter and physics beyond the standard model searching for dark matter and effects of quantum gravity the design foresees a factor of 5 10 improvement in sensitivity in the current very high energy gamma ray domain of about 100 gev to 10 tev and an extension of the accessible energy range from well below 100 gev to above 100 tev cta is a recommended project for the next decade in the us national academies of sciences 2010 decadal review in addition it is one of the magnificent seven of the european strategy for astroparticle physics published by aspera and highly ranked in the strategic plan for european astronomy leaflet of astronet click the images below to see a larger version cherenkov telescope array artist's concept related topics compact objects dark matter particle acceleration related research black holes blazars and active galactic nuclei dark matter and new physics high energy particles from space indirect dark matter detection neutron starts and pulsars kipac researchers alice allafort anna franckowiak greg madejski jim chiang joshua lande justin vandenbroucke keith bechtol marco ajello matthew wood richard dubois rob cameron rolf buehler seth digel stefan funk related links cta website the kavli foundation slac national accelerator laboratory stanford university privacy statement
